<br>
Go to the Spectre Island in OOT (get great maps from EQAtlas.com). The Gargoyles spawn around the lower part of the island, the spectres spawn at the very top. As far as I could tell, Greater Skellies are Placeholders for Gargs, so kill them as much as you can also. The Gargs sometimes drop gargoyle eyes, which are worth 8pp at a vendor. Good loot, good exp. <br>
<br>
Problem: I only camped them a couple of hours to get the eyes for Focus Item quest, and I went from being the only one there to having that tiny island swarming with 5 people.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umatches475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Matches475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(3/8/01 6:02:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gargs in OOT</span><hr size=1> I went there at lvl 16 and was fine.  At that level you have to be willing to melee with your pet, but the xp more than makes up for the dmg that you take.  The loot is very good and so is the xp, but the downside is the island's size is very small.  I was by myself when I got there, and by the time I left there were 6 other people there (all trying to solo).  Of course, when I jumped in the water to start my swim back to sister island, someone went to the top and the spectres came out to play.  Everyone died but me, so I guess that I picked the right time to leave.  If you can get the island by yourself or with one other person/group, then it is a great place, if it gets busy, save yourself a CR and leave....  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kildayin>Kildayin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(4/7/01 1:00:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gargs in OOT</span><hr size=1> As a veteran gargoyle hunter, here's what I have to say about Ocean of Tears:<br>
<br>
1. The key to this camp, all the way from 16 to 25, is patience followed by more patience.  You'll reach a point, around 24-25, where all the gargs are low blue cons and you can take two at once and have HP and mana left for a third one right away.<br>
<br>
Don't do it.<br>
<br>
Sit and rest.  Recover your mana.  The object is to leave at least one gargoyle alive at all times.  Why?  Well, as most of us know, the greater skeletons are placeholders for gargoyles.  The beautiful part of it, though, is that the gargoyles will kill the skeletons!  So, while you're resting, the gargoyles are doing your schlop work for you.  Every time a gargoyle kills a skeleton, there's a chance that a garg will spawn in place of the deceased skellie.  That makes two gargoyles running around killing skeletons.  Pretty soon, you'll have an island full of flying statues.  That's when I consider the island &quot;broken.&quot;  It's ready to be hunted at that point.<br>
<br>
2. Which leads me to a note about etiquette.  On my server, virtually no one hunts here, and I imagine that's true on the other servers as well.  So leave it ready for the next guy.  How?  When you're ready to log off, make sure there's one gargoyle still alive.  That way it'll be full of gargoyles for the next person.<br>
<br>
3. You'll be surprised how close you can get to the spectres without waking them up, but it's not something you want to be wrong about.  So be careful, but you don't have to circle the island with one foot in the water.  Don't be afraid to climb a hill, just do it with some discretion.<br>
<br>
4. For necros and SKs: Don't attempt to fear-kite here unless you (and your pet, if applicable) are levitating.  When gargoyles run, their path takes them right through the middle of the spectre camp.  Not good.  They won't wake up the spectres, but your pet will.  On the other hand, if you are levitating, you can pull WAAAAY off the island and fear-kite them back onto it.  Just don't kill them until they're actually over the island, otherwise you'll lose all those nice eyes.  And isn't that why you're here?<br>
<br>
Fear-kiting is more trouble than it's worth here.  Just stand there like a man and take your medicine.  The loot is worth it.<br>
<br>
5. Gargoyles have a narrow aggro radius.  You can almost walk right up to them before they see you and attack you.  On the other hand, they have a wide assist radius.  Be careful if you have more than one in your field of view.<br>
<br>
Which leads me to my next point...<br>
<br>
6. When they run away, DON'T LET THEM, especially if you're on the low end of the scale for this camp.  Root them, snare them, hit them with darkness, do whatever you have to do, but kill them fast.  The rough terrain can hide a nasty surprise or three.  And if you're especially slow, they'll reach the spectres.  See 4 above.<br>
<br>
7. If you're a caster, don't bind yourself on the island itself.  Bind yourself out at Sisters' Island (by the rowboat at the SW corner if you're KOS there).  That way, if you bite off more than you can chew, you can gate back there and camp before the gargoyles and/or spectres chase you down.  And it's a very short swim back.  Beats waiting for the boat again.<br>
<br>
8. Faction hits for gargoyles are as follows:<br>
Your faction standing with MayongMistmoore got worse.<br>
Your faction standing with KingTearisthex got better.<br>
Your faction standing with AgentsOfMistmoore got worse.<br>
Your faction standing with LeagueofAntonicanBards got better.<br>
Your faction standing with RingofScale got better.<br>
<br>
Make of that what you will.  King Tearis Thex, for those of you who haven't read Norrath's history, is the ruler of the elves of Felwithe.<br>
<br>
9. One final point.  Certain race/class combinations WILL NOT BE ABLE TO LEAVE WITHOUT HELP.  I note this because I, as a Teir'Dal shadowknight, fall into this category.  I am fortunate enough to have a wizard friend who can keep me invisible long enough to get on the boat.  Another way to do it is to be levitating and simply run onto the boat.  A third way is to be GG'd out, but that'll be tough to come by.  No higher-levels are going to leave their nice ancient cyclops camp just to ferry your lowbie butt around. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Depending on your race/class combination, you may be able to board a Freeport-bound boat at Brothers' Island.  I haven't tested this myself, so attempt at your own risk.<br>
<br>
Well, that's about all I have.  I hope this guide helps keep you alive and makes you all rich beyond the dreams of avarice.  Some of you, anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm not saying what server I'm on because I don't want to attract people to my island.  Didn't I tell you?  It's mine!  If you find that you ARE on my server, keep out.  I will KS you and then I will train spectres on you.  Consider yourselves notified.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Just kidding.  In all seriousness, though, this island is one of the better-kept secrets in all Norrath.  Let's keep it that way.<br>
<br>
If you see me out there, say hi.  I'll be there for a couple weeks, but if I'm not, say hi anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kildayin V'Ruuk<br>
Indigo Brotherhood<br>
