<br>
A relatively new phenomenon here (on my server, anyway) is that high-level cyclops hunters will train their visually challenged targets right through the middle.  Then they'll gate out, leaving your nice clean island overrun with jolly green giants.  When this happens, don't panic.  You'll be safe at the pull point, which is the little peninsula with a tree on it.  With some luck, you'll still be able to grab a gargoyle or two from around the cyclops, but I wouldn't plan on too much success until someone cleans it up.  Best to log off at this point and get some sleep.<br>
<br>
Kildayin V'Ruuk<br>
Indigo Brotherhood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udarkarblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkarblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(4/12/01 8:38:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gargs in OOT</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
These are also not hunted on my server. I went there when I was 18, was rough for my High Elf non-hitpoint butt. I died twice at this lvl trying these. Of course I was still learnig how to solo with my mage. I only got 2 eyes this 1st time, and killed around 6-8 of them. So I decided to kill Ogres in TD until more exp at soloing. <br>
Lvl 19 came back It was much easier. I dinged 20 real quick, and was able to take 2 evens with full/full. I stayed till I got a bubble into 20. I got 10 gargoyles eyes this time. Now I want to point out something here, gargoyles don't drop coin. They drop the eyes and some words and spell components. Out of the 10 eyes I kept 2 more for my focus items just incase and sold the rest. 8 eyes got 53pp + . After just buying my 20 spells this is a big relief to you. The eyes stack, and very low weight. I plan on going back while I still get exp. Should be much easier with 20 pets, and spells. <br>
On tactics here, fire shield your self and your pet here take some damage away from your pet here they wont die as quick. Gargs hit hard 40+ dmg. I had a nice little spot on the island. I noticed one guy said the tree spot. Well if anyone is hunting Specs this is thier spot. There is a better spot on the South East corner of the isle, it's a little part of the island that is mostly in the water. You'll know what I'm talking about if you go there. I sat here while Had my pet guard up on the island a little bit. I had him /pet guard here, right there for a reason. When I got through medding I watched him where he was looking, that told me where the closest Garg was. Pets do that when you give them that command. Then fire shield both of use, and pulled to him.  I hope this helps anyone that wants to go here. It's alot of down time but exp and loot is nice, and soloble too. Hard to find both loot and exp in the same spot. Let us Magicians stick together on this and keep it our lil secret spot.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulionfrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lionfrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(4/19/01 12:59:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Easy, if careful!</span><hr size=1> I hunted here from 18 and made it to 19 in about 3 hrs from 0 xp, I delvled when I camped on sisters island though, stupid bandits......... I never died once, not once, I was extremly careful and I found a spot that was perfect on the island, its a little phsudopod-like corner of the island directly across from the tree pulling point. I camp my pet at the extension of land and wait for a garg to come down off the hill alone and blast him, all I do is use a water pet. He might not be able to root but he can take care of himself, all you have to do is make sure you dont get aggroed. Blast, let him hit pet for awile, blast, blast, run, blast,med for about an hour and do it again (your med time may vary but thats mine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquinean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quinean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(1/14/02 2:43:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Gargs rock</span><hr size=1> All the advice posted on this thread was great. The gargs were awesome for me for 23-24. I did 21 doing the hermit in SK and compared to gargs, the hermit blew (no gnolls to contend with, no opening doors, no tricky targeting through a closed door etc.). I did 22 doing Aviak groups and the Aviaks blew (I've got your resist right here An Aviak Avocet!). There will be times when you see way too many skeles, but you'll see plenty of gargs in the long run.<br>
<br>
The spawn points for the skele/gargs (or 1 spawn point at the very least) is located straight east of the specs, about a bolt or so away. Camping a little further east of the spawn point may be a good idea, but I didn't want to try it without a partner.<br>
<br>
My first time there I camped the north end of the island, but someone trained Seafuries over to us (a necro was hunting the island also) and when I returned from my /q, one of the Seafuries had taken up residence on the island. His pathing was limited to the eastern part of the island so I camped the tree on the southwest corner and never had any problems with him.<br>
<br>
XP was pretty good, but it would have been much better had I gone there earlier. The loot was great, I came out selling 42 eyes for about 8.2pp each as a gnome with about 70 cha.<br>
<br>
The gargs could be hunted pre-20, but to truly own you should be at least 20. Evenso, if you don't come do gargs sometime pre 25, you should delete your mage as you may very possibly be an idiot.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Goedel<br>
Magician of Innoruuk<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(3/8/02 7:32:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm42.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gargs rock</span><hr size=1> I made 20 on hermit and it was cake.  Sit by the chimney.  Gnolls won't come into the compound and the hermit didn't aggro this hie until attacked.  med, buff, ds, send in pet (I used air as hermit seems to be a ranger), and nuke hard.  I died a couple times figuring it out with earth pet, but none with air.  (Albiet close a few times).<br>
<br>
Target him with /target a_hermit.  I made a hotkey.  Pet goes through cabin walls, nukes work through cabin walls, and he always died where I could reach the corpse, (sometimes using the /target a_hermit, /loot commands).<br>
<br>
